name: Patrick Mahomes
summary: Patrick Mahomes, quarterback for the Kansas City Chiefs, was fined $14,112 for unsportsmanlike conduct during the game against the Buffalo Bills. The fine was issued after Mahomes made a "violent gesture" towards the Bills' sideline following a touchdown celebration. Mahomes' connection with Travis Kelce for a 27-yard gain ended with a high-point catch. The NFL has fined Mahomes for his actions, which were deemed to be in violation of its unsportsmanlike conduct rules. Mahomes has expressed his desire for the Chiefs to have more "blowouts" following the team's narrow win over the Bills.
